      passage: `India has classified the spiraling whitefly as an invasive species that could harm some of the country&rsquo;s native species. But researchers Alejandro Camacho and Jason McLachlan have pointed out that &ldquo;invasive&rdquo; and &ldquo;native&rdquo; are labels that describe temporary circumstances. Changes in Earth&rsquo;s climate may force animals from their current ranges. Climate changes may also create good habitats in areas where a species couldn&rsquo;t live previously. In the case of India, these observations suggest that ______`,
