      passage: `With some elements, like selenium, scientists were able to isolate a relatively pure sample of the substance shortly after discovering its existence&mdash;but this wasn&rsquo;t the case with all elements. ______ the isolation process took a few years. The element molybdenum, for instance, was discovered in 1778 but not isolated until 1781.`,
